  "text": "## Comprehensive Trace of SSO Settings Control in Grafana v11.4.0\n\nThe ssoSettingsApi feature flag is implemented end-to-end across four architectural layers that work together to gate and enforce SSO configuration control:\n\n### Layer 1: Feature Flag Definition\n\nThe feature flag is defined in `pkg/services/featuremgmt/toggles_gen.go` (auto-generated from `registry.go`):\n- **FlagSsoSettingsApi** (line 508): \"Enables the SSO settings API and the OAuth configuration UIs in Grafana\"\n- **FlagSsoSettingsLDAP** (line 712): \"Use the new SSO Settings API to configure LDAP\"\n- **FlagSsoSettingsSAML** (line 624): \"Use the new SSO Settings API to configure the SAML connector\"\n\n### Layer 2: SSO Settings Infrastructure\n\nThe infrastructure layer provides the core interfaces and data models:\n\n**Interfaces** (`pkg/services/ssosettings/ssosettings.go`):\n- **Service**: Management interface with methods to List, Get, Upsert, Delete, and Patch SSO settings, plus RegisterReloadable for live configuration reloading\n- **Reloadable**: Interface for providers to validate and reload settings when they change\n- **FallbackStrategy**: Interface for loading settings from legacy sources (config files, environment variables) for backwards compatibility\n- **Store**: Database persistence interface\n\n**Data Model** (`pkg/services/ssosettings/models/models.go`):\n- **SSOSettings**: Struct with xorm ORM annotations for database persistence\n  - `xorm:\"id pk\"` for primary key\n  - `xorm:\"provider\"` for OAuth provider identifier\n  - `xorm:\"settings\"` for JSON settings object\n  - Soft delete via `xorm:\"is_deleted\"`\n  - Table name: `sso_setting`\n- **SettingsSource**: Enum distinguishing database vs system (config file) sources\n\n**Persistence** (`pkg/services/ssosettings/database/database.go`):\n- **SSOSettingsStore**: Implements Store interface using xorm-based database transactions\n  - Get, List, Upsert, Delete operations with soft-delete support\n  - Filters by `is_deleted` column for logical deletion\n\n**Fallback Strategies** (`pkg/services/ssosettings/strategies/`):\n- **OAuthStrategy**: Loads OAuth provider configs from cfg.SSOSettingsConfigurableProviders and legacy OAuth config settings\n- **LDAPStrategy**: Loads LDAP config from cfg.LDAP* settings for backwards compatibility\n- **SAMLStrategy**: Loads SAML settings from licensed provider config\n\nThese strategies enable the system to function with both legacy (file-based) and new (database-backed) SSO configurations simultaneously.\n\n### Layer 3: API & Authentication Wiring\n\n**REST API Endpoints** (`pkg/services/ssosettings/api/api.go`):\n- **Route**: `/api/v1/sso-settings`\n- **Endpoints**:\n  - `GET /` - List all SSO settings with redacted secrets (requires `ActionSettingsRead`)\n  - `GET /:key` - Get SSO settings for a provider (requires `ActionSettingsRead` with provider scope)\n  - `PUT /:key` - Update/upsert SSO settings (requires `ActionSettingsWrite` with provider scope)\n  - `DELETE /:key` - Delete SSO settings (soft delete, requires `ActionSettingsWrite` with provider scope)\n- All endpoints are protected with access control middleware using:\n  - `ac.EvalPermission(ac.ActionSettingsRead/Write, ac.ScopeSettingsOAuth(key))` evaluators\n  - Access checks filter settings by provider scope\n\n**Feature Flag Gating** (`pkg/services/ssosettings/ssosettingsimpl/service.go`):\n- **Critical Control Point** (lines 94-96):\n  ```go\n  if features.IsEnabledGlobally(featuremgmt.FlagSsoSettingsApi) {\n    ssoSettingsApi := api.ProvideApi(svc, routeRegister, ac)\n    ssoSettingsApi.RegisterAPIEndpoints()\n  }\n  ```\n  The entire REST API endpoint registration is **gated by FlagSsoSettingsApi**. When the flag is disabled, the `/api/v1/sso-settings` endpoints are not registered at all.\n\n**Conditional Provider Support** (same file, lines 63-75):\n- LDAP provider is added to the providers list when `FlagSsoSettingsLDAP` is enabled\n- SAML provider is added when licensed and `FlagSsoSettingsSAML` is enabled\n- These control which providers appear in the SSO settings API responses\n\n**Fallback Strategies Wiring** (lines 51-54):\n- OAuth, LDAP (conditional), and SAML (conditional) fallback strategies are registered\n- These enable loading settings from legacy config sources when not yet migrated to database\n\n**Authentication Client Registration** (`pkg/services/authn/authnimpl/registration.go`):\n- **LDAP Client Conditional Registration** (lines 56-61):\n  ```go\n  ssoSettingsLDAP := features.IsEnabledGlobally(featuremgmt.FlagSsoSettingsApi) && \n                     features.IsEnabledGlobally(featuremgmt.FlagSsoSettingsLDAP)\n  if cfg.LDAPAuthEnabled || ssoSettingsLDAP {\n    ldap := clients.ProvideLDAP(cfg, ldapService, userService, authInfoService)\n    proxyClients = append(proxyClients, ldap)\n    passwordClients = append(passwordClients, ldap)\n  }\n  ```\n  LDAP authentication is registered when either legacy LDAP is enabled OR both SSO settings API and LDAP feature flags are enabled.\n\n- **OAuth Client Auto-Registration** (lines 98-101):\n  ```go\n  for name := range socialService.GetOAuthProviders() {\n    clientName := authn.ClientWithPrefix(name)\n    authnSvc.RegisterClient(clients.ProvideOAuth(clientName, cfg, oauthTokenService, \n                            socialService, settingsProviderService, features))\n  }\n  ```\n  OAuth clients are auto-registered for all providers. The OAuth client internally loads provider configuration from `socialService.GetOAuthInfoProvider()`, which pulls from SSO settings when FlagSsoSettingsApi is enabled.\n\n### Layer 4: Access Control & DI Registration\n\n**Permission Actions** (`pkg/services/accesscontrol/roles.go`):\n- **ActionSettingsRead**: Used to grant read access to SSO settings\n- **ActionSettingsWrite**: Used to grant write access to SSO settings\n- **ScopeSettingsOAuth(key)**: Scoped access to specific OAuth provider settings\n\n**Role Definitions** (same file):\n- **SettingsReaderRole** (fixed:settings:reader):\n  - Grants `ActionSettingsRead` with `ScopeSettingsAll`\n  - Applied to admin UI for viewing SSO configurations\n\n**Complete Dependency Injection** (`pkg/services/ssosettings/ssosettingsimpl/service.go`):\nThe ProvideService function orchestrates the entire system:\n1. Creates SSOSettingsStore (database persistence)\n2. Registers fallback strategies for legacy config compatibility\n3. Conditionally adds LDAP and SAML to supported providers based on feature flags\n4. **Conditionally registers REST API** when FlagSsoSettingsApi is enabled\n5. Wires secrets service for encryption/decryption\n6. Registers metrics and usage stats collection\n\n## Evidence Chain for Compliance Audits\n\nThis architecture demonstrates complete control-flow gating:\n\n1. **Feature Flag Enforcement**: FlagSsoSettingsApi must be explicitly enabled for the API to be registered\n2. **API Protection**: All endpoints require access control evaluation with specific OAuth permissions\n3. **Authentication Client Gating**: LDAP registration depends on both FlagSsoSettingsApi and FlagSsoSettingsLDAP\n4. **Database Persistence**: SSO settings are stored in the `sso_setting` table with audit timestamps (created, updated)\n5. **Fallback Strategy**: Legacy config sources are supported but can be migrated to database-backed settings\n6. **Live Reloading**: Reloadable interface allows providers to validate and reload settings when changed via API\n\nThe control is enforced at multiple levels: feature flag registration, API endpoint registration, authentication client registration, and permission evaluation. Disabling FlagSsoSettingsApi effectively disables the entire SSO settings management capability while preserving legacy authentication mechanisms."
